Make sure you wash your hands well.
We all know that you need to wash them (e.g. after coming home or before a meal).
But not everyone knows that in order to actually get rid of germs, you need to do it in the right way.
This is especially important now that autumn infections are approaching.
It takes at least 30-40 seconds for washing to sufficiently remove dangerous bacteria and viruses from our hands
And most of us are shorter.
Warm water and regular soap are enough – it is not true that it must be antibacterial (many doctors even advise against it).
When washing, we rub not only the bottoms and tops of the hands, but also: the tips of the fingers (jointed or single) – rub them with circular movements on the inside of the second hand, the spaces between the fingers (interleave the hands, rubbing the fingers against each other), thumbs – each thumb we cover with the other hand and in such a hug we cover the neck with the right hand.
In an emergency situation (when you can not wash your hands), you should wipe your hands with a wet wipe, and then use an antibacterial gel (in drugstores, from 5 z<0xC5><0x82>).
