UBS: Gold close to the equilibrium point
“The euro exchange rate will remain at the level of PLN 4.35 in the coming months, which will be accompanied by a weak economic situation in global markets,” said Michael Bolliger of UBS Wealth Management.
“Expectations of maintaining a solid economic growth rate and stable monetary policy speak in favour of stabilising the zloty’s quotations at the current ceiling,” the expert said in an interview with Bankier.pl.
In his opinion, despite the clear inflationary pressure, the Monetary Policy Council will not decide to raise rates in an environment where the vast majority of central banks are easing policy.
“If the zloty is properly priced – euro quotations should continue in the coming months around the ceiling of PLN 4.35 – according to him, Polish bonds are not very attractive.
Bonds from emerging markets offer much more favorable yields than Polish securities,” says Michael Bolliger, Head of Asset Allocation for Emerging Markets at UBS Wealth Management.
