The Senate has decided on key legislation.
The Senate passed without amendment the law on disclosure of the assets of the families of the most important state officials and on the flights of the most important people in the country.
52 senators voted in favor of the amendment to the law on the property of families of state officials – without amendments, 14 were against, three abstained.
Thus, the senators decided to reject the 12 amendments tabled during Wednesday’s debate by Senator S<0xC5><0x82>awomir Rybicki.
According to him, the amendments were to “civilize” and limit the scope of the information provided in the statement on the financial situation of their own children, the children of the spouse, children adapted to cases where the children remain in a common household with a person obliged to make a statement.
The Act on the Disclosure of the Property of the Families of the Most Important State Officials, the draft of which was created in the Prime Minister’s Office, was adopted by the Sejm on 11 September.
The provisions assume that, among others, the Prime Minister, ministers, deputies, senators, presidents of the Constitutional Court, the Supreme Administrative Court and the Supreme Court, as well as persons at the head of other state institutions, will be required to include in the property statement information about the personal property of spouses, children and persons remaining in the joint spouse.
The Senate also did not propose amendments to the law on the flights of the most important people in the country.
It regulates which flights have HEAD status and who can be on board government planes with the most important people in the country.
The law also specifies who is responsible for maintaining the Central Register of Flights.
Fifty-five senators voted in favor of the bill, 12 opposed it, and four abstained.
According to the bill, any flight of the president will be a flight “performed in an official mission.”
The flight will be accompanied by family members and other persons invited by the President.
On the other hand, the flight in the official mission of the Prime Minister and the Marshals of the Sejm and Senate will be only a flight “carried out in order to carry out tasks directly related to the function performed”.
The law also specifies the list of people who can accompany the most important people in the country during the flight.
According to regulations, members of the delegation may be on board the aircraft – invited deputies, senators, representatives of public authorities and experts; persons providing technical, medical or organizational services; as well as journalists.
According to the law, in case of doubts related to the flights of the Marshals of the Sejm and Senate, the head of the KPRM will ask for their explanation.
If such doubts are not clarified within the prescribed time, the head of the KPRM will be obliged to notify the heads of the Sejm or Senate offices of the impossibility of organizing such a flight.
